  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0dc3\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A stick for the coconuts that the Panadura council bought from the Divulapitiya council",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It was discussed in the meeting of the Divulapitiya Regional Council that the officials of the Divulapitiya Regional Council have faced an audit problem due to the non-payment of more than seven hundred thousand rupees for a stock of coconuts that the Panadura Regional Council acquired to provide relief to the people of Panadura during the spread of the Corona epidemic.",
        "In the months of March and April 2020, the Divulapitiya Regional Council has provided the coconut stock at the request of the Panadura Regional Council and the amount of Rs.",
        "Mr. Divulapitiya Regional Chairman Mr. Indika Jayasinghe informed the MPs that after two and a half years, the Panadura Council sent a letter saying that the relevant coconut stock was small and spoiled, and proposed to pay only two hundred thousand rupees.",
        "The chairman said that if the Panadura council does not pay this amount, it will be charged from its officials and it has been informed that the money will be given as soon as possible for the services rendered to the people at the time of trouble."
      ],
